-- @id(OCL-TEST-EVERY-IMPL-ID-HAS-TEST)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-LINK)
-- Every implementation-bearing model element should be verified by at least
-- one linked test of the layer its kind expects (§5.1 taxonomy). This is the
-- structural coverage invariant behind USE-TEST-COVERAGE. Safe-by-default:
-- the rule is enforced only when the profile has configured layers, and then a
-- violation blocks when test.gate = error and warns when gate = warn; with no
-- configured layers it is inert. Cycle A enforces the existence/linkage shape
-- only — no test is executed.
context TestLink
inv EveryImplIdHasTest:
  ModelElement.allInstances()->select(e | e.isImplementationBearing)->forAll(e |
    TestLink.allInstances()->exists(t |
      t.model_id = e.id and t.layer = e.expectedLayer))

-- @id(OCL-TEST-LAYER-IN-PROFILE)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-LINK)
-- A test link's layer and (when present) framework must be members of the
-- configured test profile (config.test.layers) — the invariant behind
-- USE-TEST-LAYER-MEMBERSHIP that replaces the silent drop of non-playwright
-- frameworks. When no layers are configured the membership cannot be checked
-- and the rule is vacuously satisfied, so a profile-less repo is never wrongly
-- blocked.
context TestLink
inv LayerInProfile:
  TestConfig.layers->notEmpty() implies
    (TestConfig.layers->exists(l | l.name = self.layer)
     and (self.framework->notEmpty() implies
          TestConfig.layers->exists(l | l.name = self.layer and l.framework = self.framework)))

-- @id(OCL-TEST-PROFILE-CONFIRMED)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-DETECTION)
-- A layer's framework must be operator-confirmed before its tests are
-- authored — detection RECOMMENDS, it never silently writes config (the
-- /mdd-deploy dialect rule). A detected layer with an unresolved ambiguity is
-- surfaced as a blocking question, not auto-picked (USE-TEST-PROFILE-DETECT).
context DetectedProfile
inv ProfileConfirmedBeforeAuthoring:
  self.ambiguities->notEmpty() implies self.requiresOperatorConfirmation = true

-- @id(OCL-TEST-GREEN-GATE)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-PLAN-STEP)
-- A still-red test at cycle close blocks closure when test.gate = error and
-- merely warns (allowing a user-accepted close) when test.gate = warn — the
-- opt-down mirroring security.parity_check (USE-TEST-GREEN-GATE). This governs
-- the GREEN side only; the red->green requirement (Cycle C) is non-negotiable.
context GreenGateReport
inv StillRedBlocksUnderError:
  (self.all_green = false and TestConfig.gate = ParityMode::Error)
    implies self.blocking = true

-- @id(OCL-TEST-RED-EVIDENCE-RECORDED)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-EVIDENCE)
-- NON-NEGOTIABLE. Every gap @id (an objective element absent from current at
-- cycle open) must have a gap_tests entry in .mdd/cycles/<N>/test-evidence.yml
-- whose red phase was observed FAILING (exit_code != 0) before its implementing
-- code. The evidence is the runner's own output, not a heuristic. No config
-- disables this (USE-TEST-RED-PHASE).
context GapTest
inv RedObservedBeforeCode:
  self.isGap implies
    (self.red->notEmpty() and self.red.result = TestPhaseResult::Fail
     and self.red.exit_code <> 0)

-- @id(OCL-TEST-RED-THEN-GREEN-TO-CLOSE)
-- @ref(DOM-TEST-EVIDENCE)
-- NON-NEGOTIABLE. A cycle closes only when every gap @id shows fail THEN pass:
-- red.result = Fail then green.result = Pass (exit_code == 0). This has no
-- config off-switch — distinct from test.gate, which governs only the green
-- side (USE-TEST-RED-GREEN-GATE). An empty gap set (pure refactor) closes on
-- the green gate alone; non-negotiable means every NEW behaviour proves
-- red->green, not that every cycle invents a failure.
context RedGreenReport
inv RedThenGreenRequiredToClose:
  self.satisfied = true implies
    (self.missing_evidence->isEmpty()
     and self.not_red_first->isEmpty()
     and self.still_red->isEmpty())
